aweme_list.desc: Do you know when a Humpback is eating sardines or krill? When Humpbacks are vertically lunge feeding like in this video they are eating small fish such as sardines or anchovies. When Humpbacks are side lunging or skimming they are most likely eating krill, which is a crustacean shrimp-looking creature. Do you know when a Humpback is eating sardines or krill? When Humpbacks are vertically lunge feeding like in this video they are eating small fish such as sardines or anchovies. When Humpbacks are side lunging or skimming they are most likely eating krill, which is a crustacean shrimp-looking creature. Today we saw one of out first vertical lunge feeding of the year, which means that sardines and anchovies are coming back to the bay just in time for the hungry Humpback's Summer banquets!
